                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d610">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A 4e/18: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-07T14:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 7, 1922—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 7—8:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1. Present tariff revision calculated form basis for subsequent 2½ percent
                    surtax, also questions concerning reclassifications and basis assessing duties
                    will be considered. Anticipate require four to six months. Important our
                    Government send immediately technical expert as assistant. Chinese request names
                    American associate delegates. Japanese sending two well-qualified technical
                    assistants. Request authorization nominate local American business man as member
                    commission similar to action British, French and Italian interests. First formal
                    meeting Commission April 12th. Arnold.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
